items.name: Bossfight Diffusion
items.description:
Generate epic bosses and bossfights with this embedding!

You can use this embedding to create large monsters/creatures, and an "adventurer" in the foreground if you wish. Including the word "fight" in your prompt can help with including that second character. It works fairly well with models like Dreamshaper, Dreamlike Diffusion, Roboetics mix, etc.

Please share with me what you make, I'd love to see your epic bosses!

items.name: Kratos
items.description:
Used the Joepenna DreamBooth repo and trained on Dreamlike Diffusion 1.0. It is trained on some renders of his 2018 character model without his beard to give flexibility with his facial hair.

  • Prompt with token and class "kratos person".

  • Prompt for facial hairs like beard, shaven, goatee, etc.

  • Fix faces with Upscale R-ESRGAN 4x+ and inpaint at a lower dimension with "Only Masked" checked.

  • Run your photomode shots of him through img2img.

items.name: Hanako (artist) Style
items.description:
LORA trained on 83 images of artist はなこ (Hanako) - https://www.pixiv.net/en/users/15141389 on relatively low amount of steps.

Doesn't require trigger words, recommended weight is 1.

Training and dataset parameters:

  • Images are scrapped from Pixiv (sketches excluded), tagged by WD tagger;

  • Trained using kohya-ss LORA training GUI, rank 32, resolution 512x768, no regularisation folder, other settings were default;

  • Trained on anything-v4.5-pruned-fp16 model;

  • 34 epochs, 1 step per image.

items.name: Allison Mack LoRA
items.description:
A Stable Diffusion LoRA profile based on Federal Correctional Institution, Dublin's most famous inmate, Allison Mack (also, she was in Smallville).

Place it in "stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora" folder in Automatic1111 WebUI root folder.

Made using kohya-ss.

In txt2img, under "Additional Networks", select "Enable" and under Model 1 select "Allison Mack" and assign a weight between 0.3-0.7 (feel free to experiment!). In the prompt text window use "Allison Mack" within your prompt to generate images.

Embed has been trained on Stable Diffusion 1.5 model.

I Recommend the model https://civitai.com/models/4922/grapelikedreamfruit - Gives amazing realistic renders.

items.name: Beautiful Asian Pop Star Yang Chaoyue 杨超越
items.description:
Trained on 16 images, mostly close-up portrait of Chinese actress/pop singer 杨超越 Yang Chaoyue. Processed with focal point crop. Weight this embedding at 0.8~1.2 is suggested. See sample images and png info to grab some prompts that just works.

Hires.fix on is suggested (e.g. 512*768--2x-->1024*1536, Hires steps 18,Denoising strength 0.15, ESRGAN_4x or LDSR are highly suggested as always, depending on trade-off between speed and super-sharp details.)

Try out Restore Faces when generating side view photos since the training set isn't varied enough concerning poses and angle, though it performs quite well on contrapposto or selfie photos.

中文翻译 Simplified Chinese Translation:

训练了 16 张图像，大部分是中国女演员/流行歌手 杨超越的特写肖像。使用焦点裁剪处理。建议将此嵌入权重设置为 0.8~1.2。查看示例图像和 png 信息以获取一些有效的提示。

建议启用 Hires.fix超分辨率（例如 512*768--2x-->1024*1536，Hires 步骤 18，去噪强度 0.15，一如既往地强烈建议 ESRGAN_4x 或 LDSR，取决于你在速度和细节之间的权衡)

在生成侧视图照片时尝试 Restore Faces，因为训练集在姿势和角度方面的变化不够大，尽管它在 contrapposto 或自拍照片上表现相当不错。

请勿用于商业用途或生成违法/侵权照片用于传播。

Astolfo from Fate series, you know who he is. Use dk_astolfo in your prompt to activate the embedding.

I've tested on this embedding on multiple anime models and most of them worked just fine. The only problem is there's not much yaoi or otoko_no_ko content in them, so using 1girl tag in negative prompts should handle most of the problems of generating otoko_no_ko characters.

Those listed models below have been tested and got great results with them so far:

items.name: Akari Watanabe
items.description:
This is my new Model! If you want your own style/person trained, just DM me with a dataset of ~20 imgs on discord Flonix#4022 and ill train it for you!

Lora made on Capivara's Akira Dataset, set the weight lower than 1 to get it to follow your prompt more. Also remember to set CLIP skip to 2.

example prompt:

in the distance ona hill, akariWatanabe anime woman, wedding dress
Negative prompt: hands
Steps: 20, Sampler: Euler a, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 2494829530, Size: 512x624, Model hash: a7bd5ab091, Denoising strength: 0.36, Clip skip: 2, ENSD: 31337, AddNet Enabled: True, AddNet Module 1: LoRA, AddNet Model 1: akariWatanabe(a99b2cfff4c1), AddNet Weight A 1: 1, AddNet Weight B 1: 1, Hires upscale: 2, Hires upscaler: 4x_foolhardy_Remacri
Keep in mind this is a LoRA, so you need to use it as such. It's not a standalone model and it's not a TI.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

usage by @Lykon

items.name: SCG Emotions Pack - Simple embeds for  easily controlling a variety of emotions! (For all 1.5 Models and Merges)
items.description:
Recently I released my embedding toolkit which has a variety of tools and fixers I've come up with over the past 6 months. I considered adding my emotion embeds to that listing, however I want to keep that specific to helper tools, so I've decided to break this emotion pack into it's own listing.

I've designed these embeds to be lightweight and easy to use. Just add the emotion pack you want right next to your subject name as follows:

a portrait of a Happy512 clown

While they will likely still work if you plop them in other places in your prompt, they work best when they are placed just preceding your subject.

As with my toolkit, your results may vary. I make no guarantees, however I have been using these for awhile now and they seem pretty consistent, especially when mixed with my other embeddings available on my civit page. Follow me here on Civit to be notified when I release new embeddings!

--------

To use these embeddings in AUTOMATIC1111, copy them to your embeddings folder in your stable-diffusion-webui directory. No need to restart, just invoke the embedding from your prompt. Make sure you are using a 1.5 version compatible model or you will get errors!

--------

modelVersions.name: Happy512
modelVersions.description: Happy512 - creates easy smiles. neg teeth if you don't want a toothy smile

modelVersions.name: Smile512
modelVersions.description: Creates nice, toothy smiles. Neg teeth if the smiles are too big. Very similar to Happy512, just a bigger smile.

modelVersions.name: Grin512
modelVersions.description: Big cheesy grins, eyes squinting, and happiness. Very very similar to Laugh512.

modelVersions.name: Laugh512
modelVersions.description: Big laughs, head back, mouth open, eyes closed. Can sometimes create the "shark effect" with multiple rows of teeth. You can try negging teeth, but it alters the way this embed outputs if you do that, so rerolling may be your best bet if you get a sharky grin.

modelVersions.name: Nervous512
modelVersions.description: General sense of unease. Sometimes can look a little shocked, but my goal was mostly just "uncomfortable".

modelVersions.name: Shock512
modelVersions.description: Holy shit!!!! (this is what I'm trying to capture)

modelVersions.name: Defiance512
modelVersions.description: Arms crossed, stern looks. This is the face of the protestor standing firm, or the petulant child refusing to clean her room. I also get a bit of "disappointed mom after coming home late" vibe too, though it wasn't my intention. this can be a fun one!

modelVersions.name: Angry512
modelVersions.description:
Yep. They're pissed. This one comes on a little heavy sometimes, if you find it's too much, just de-emphasize it to 0.9 or so like this:

(Angry512:0.9)

Also, this one tends to favor masculinity, I don't have too many problems with it changing women to men, but if you just feed it "person" it's going to give you a man pretty much every time.

modelVersions.name: Sad512
modelVersions.description: Sadness, loneliness, despair. This one likes to sap the color out of images, so if you want color, you'll need to prompt it (or neg "grayscale"). Can create tears sometimes as well, neg them if you don't want wet cheeks!

items.name: Kaguya-sama：Love Is War  伊井野弥子/Iino Miko
Florence Nightingale (Fate) Lora
items.description:
Based on Florence Nightingale from the Fate franchise

Trained on AOM2

Use weight 0.9-1 for included outfits. Weights 0.5-0.8 recommended for other clothing as the included outfits are more likely to overfit otherwise.

Supports Nightingale's Original, Trick or Treatment and Chaldea Lifesavers outfits. Use the tags below to activate each:

Original: military uniform

Trick or Treatment: slingshot bikini, green gloves, nurse cap, skirt, thighhighs

Chaldea Lifesavers: swimsuit, yellow bikini, side-tie bikini bottom (unique bikini top shape not recreated)

Also, I recommend adding (syringe) to your negative prompts.

items.name: POV Squatting Cowgirl LoRA [1 MB]
items.description:
This is another simple sex position LoRA for POV Squatting Cowgirl.

USE CLIP SKIP 2.

I suggest using this LoRA at 0.9-1.0 weight for best results.

Always add this prompt to activate it: <lora:PSCowgirl:0.9>, 1boy, penis, squatting cowgirl position, vaginal, pov

After that you can add other descriptive tags - If you remove penis from the prompt - It will give the effect of deeper penetration.

If you remove penis and vaginal - It will give the effect of her just sitting on you. If she is wearing a skirt or something similar - It will feel like it's implied sex - especially if you add cum.

If you add squatting to the prompt - It will show more of the position and it's a wider shot.

This was trained on NAI model - I have no idea if it works on realistic models. Images were generated on Corneo's 7th Heaven Mix using the Orange Mix VAE.

Embeds and LoRA used: Bad Prompt - Misty - Bea

Be sure to leave a comment, review and check out my other stuff here - you might like it.

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune

items.name: Evelyn Nobody
items.description:
Follow me to make sure you see new poses and Nobodys when I post them. Things move fast on this site, it's easy to miss.

Meet Evelyn Nobody, this person doesn't exist. You may think she looks like someone you know, but she isn't. Just the imprecise nature of diffusion. Stylized images were generated using the legendary A to Zovya RPG Artist's Tools model.

If you need a consistent character but don't want a known celebrity, Evelyn is your gal.

Follow me for more of the Nobody family coming soon for 1.5 and 2.1.

Click the zNobody tag for more, or the Nobody tag to see other's contributions.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

items.name: Son Goku - Dragon Ball Z / Super (LoRA)
items.description:
For this model, I mostly just tried to teach it the appearance of his different forms. NovalAI/Anything already knows enough about Goku to use this model at lower settings, such as 0.5 or 0.6.

This model is somewhat janky so don't get your hopes up too much

It was trained on his base form, super saiyan, super saiyan 3, super saiyan god, super saiyan blue, and mastered ultra instinct. Most forms work decently enough, but Super Saiyan 3 has a lot of issues.

items.name: Granblue Fantasy Tweyen / Song LoRA
items.description:
The first LoRA I ever made. Hideously overfit, set weight down to like .4. But it otherwise works just fine. The trigger word isn't even necessary really.

I train all my LoRAs on base NAI and with FULL TAGS. That means it should work on any models that have NAI in their ancestry (almost all anime models today), but you MUST tag things to get things.

items.name: Skin Diamond
items.description:
Skin Diamond

This is another TI off my list ;)

I trained her for 10,000 steps and found the 3k-5k range looks the best to me. This upload represents the 5000 step version. I used 45 pictures, quite easy to find if you know where to look,

I used the base v1.5 SD model for training, but highly recommend using any of the top rated checkpoints here.

PLEASE send along any tips and advice you have, I want to make this model as good and foolproof as possible, thanks!

NOTE: Not gonna lie, this was difficult to pull off because (1) most of the very best and most life like gens were nsfw. (Don't know why that would happen) and (2) because of her heritage (her father is Eritrean) the tendency is for her for to come out looking more Asian than African. I'm going to keep working and update when possible.

Do you like my work? Buy me a beer!

items.name: Shu Qi - Taiwan/HK actress/model
items.description:
Shu Qi - Taiwan/HK actress and model

It took me a LOT of tries but I think I've got a decent Shu Qi (chinese 舒淇) textual inversion to offer you. Shu Qi is best known to western audiences as the gal in the first Transporter movie. She started her career doing softcore movies like Sex and Zen but moved quickly to more mainstream movies. She was in the final running for Zhang Ziyi's role in Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon, and starred opposite Jackie Chan in Gorgeous. On top of garnering a number of acting awards, she's still a staple of Asian fashion magazines and commercials. This TI represents her look from about about 2005-2015. I might do another one for her very early period.

About the TI, this is trained on 44 images against 3 vectors. It took a long time to figure out because I kept overtraining and later discovered the best takes were VERY low in the training process (like only 1300 steps). It was trained using SD1.5, pretty standard.

Intended for use with a photorealistic model, I get good likenesses of Shu Qi using RealisticVision1.3, adjust the weighting as needed up to 1.2-1.3 depending on your surrounding prompt.

As you can see from examples, her look is versatile, whether doing a red carpet render, a John Woo type action movie, or in the bedroom for a different type of action...

Download and drop the broc-shuqi.pt file in your ..\stable-diffusion-webui\embeddings folder and add the name of the file (without the .pt part) to your prompt to activate. You can of course change the name of the file to whatever you want and use that for your prompt instead if you prefer.

items.name: Jim Lee (DC Comics / Marvel) Style LoRA
items.description:
Jim Lee (DC Comics / Marvel) style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

Been wanting to try this for a long time now. I think this came out pretty nicely and captures the style of Jim Lee quite well. I tested it on AnyLoRA and AbyssOrangeMix2 with my negative embeddings and it's pretty convincing at weight=1 for the offset version and 0.65 for the original (check "original" tab for a comparison). Use the prompt jim lee for better accuracy.

Keep in mind that, while this can make Superman, Batman and Wonder Woman pretty well, this is not a character LoRa but a Style LoRA. Have fun making your own superheroes!

NOTE: I used ControlNet on some of the examples. Check the full generation data.

2nd pic courtesy of sadxzero from the reviews.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions of the model (by default it's :1)

items.name: Extra Breasts
items.description:
If booba good, then surely more booba more good, right?

NEW: Are four breasts a bit overkill for you? Would you prefer a bit less? Are you a huge fan of a certain scene in a 1990 Arnold Schwarzenegger flick set on Mars? Then check out Extra Breasts: Triple Trouble!

HOW TO USE: Current version is designed primarily for 4 breasts and does not use any trigger words. Select in Additional Networks or add to your prompt and go. Designed for use at 1.0 weight with NAI-based/anime models; for realistic models you may want to increase weight to 1.2 or 1.25.

Works great with topless/nude subjects, or subjects with clothing that fully covers the breasts (shirts, sweaters).

Works...not so great with skimpy clothing (e.g. bras, bikinis). My guess is that drawing a double bikini is something that is much harder for the A.I. to infer than just slightly changing the contours of a shirt or sweater. It still sometimes works at high (>=1.25) weights, though!

It's generally a good idea to add extra arms to your negative prompt...unless you're into that, of course.

ALPHA VERSION 0.2.4: Retrained exclusively on 4 breasts this time. This gives vastly more consistent results with both realistic and anime models, and interestingly enough will still sometimes output 6 or 8 at higher weights.

FUTURE PLANS: Unless I can find a way to more consistently control breast count using trigger words, future LORA releases will likely be designed for a specific count (e.g. one for 3 breasts, one for 4, one for 6, etc.).
